name":"ken-christensen","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/6e13fe8d600b157fb23446500a1c2a29147857fa1e20e23e5c824ce71e1b0630\/bzf6bbrw7.jpg","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/6e13fe8d600b157fb23446500a1c2a29147857fa1e20e23e5c824ce71e1b0630\/bzf6bbrw7.jpg"},"badges":[],"verified":1,"is_verified_user":true,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"is_owner":1,"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_claim_authorship":0,"can_accept_authorship":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"fork_id":null,"url":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/view\/lr-clonase-reaction-for-multisite-gateway-cloning-bn8gmhtw","forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"7A53E5E019F611EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","state_version_id":383,"steps":[{"id":1065984,"guid":"7E1983F019F711EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"99C2E7A095DA41CEA3CE8E715A014A81","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Reaction Setup"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F744313F455448329D82818671AAE49F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For multi-fragment (i.e. 2-, 3-, or 4-fragment recombination) reactions, use an equimolar amount of each entry clone. We recommend 10 fmol of each entry clone and 10 fmol of DEST vector per 5 \u03bcl reaction.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Plasmid mixture:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add the following components to a 1.5-ml microcentrifuge tube at room temperature and mix. Use this reaction mixture in the following procedure.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Entry clones (10 fmoles)*<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Destination vector (10 fmoles) <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">at least 1 \u03bcl 1X TE buffer, pH 8.0 for a<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold;\"> <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">total volume of 4\u00b5l<\/span><span><\/span><\/li><\/ol><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">*All entry clones (two, three or four, depending on the type of reaction) must be included. The total of all plasmids and buffer combined should not exceed 4 \u03bcl.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Use a calculator to determine the amount of each plasmid to add to the reaction. For example, you would need to add 29 ng of a 4.25 kb plasmid to get 10 fmol. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.promega.com\/resources\/tools\/biomath\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">https:\/\/www.promega.com\/resources\/tools\/biomath\/<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1066022,"guid":"731DADF019FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","previous_id":1065984,"previous_guid":"7E1983F019F711EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"767BB5777F7244E8A5D62D6A75C9845F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Procedure"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A3DD702EB4C743C7BED2CDCA09B3E596","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove LR Clonase\u2122 II Plus enzyme mix from freezer and thaw on ice for about <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. Vortex the enzyme mix briefly twice (2 seconds each).<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"10C469E019FD11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":120,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":58320,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":120},{"id":1066023,"guid":"731F0D8119FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","previous_id":1066022,"previous_guid":"731DADF019FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"568D09B5CB324737B313F057E5260FA7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Procedure"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9AB00155D75D48B59CEAB83EE50D22D6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">To each MultiSite or MultiSite Pro LR reaction mixture, add 1 \u03bcl of LR Clonase\u2122 II Plus and mix well by vortexing briefly twice. Microcentrifuge briefly.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":58320,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1066024,"guid":"7320E24019FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","previous_id":1066023,"previous_guid":"731F0D8119FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"692C04644922456C9F7ACF84DC4E4EEE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Procedure"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E74C2F2441E9493E9571F466F224D24A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Return enzyme mix to freezer immediately after use. The enzyme mix can be stored at -20\u00b0C for up to 6 months or at -80\u00b0C for long-term storage.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":58320,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1066025,"guid":"7322B70019FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","previous_id":1066024,"previous_guid":"7320E24019FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A8B16A6EB2324968AA8AD8F3143E2237","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Procedure"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A3E8A1345E584F41B6A2AF3BE556F6B0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Incubate recombination reaction at 25\u00b0C for <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"1C793D6019FD11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":57600,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":58320,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":57600},{"id":1066026,"guid":"7325280019FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","previous_id":1066027,"previous_guid":"441E517019FD11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1485C3EA5CCD40C5BF2BA39E3BA0B6A7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transformation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F2518BA52B104300B063C79AFF592CB7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>For 2- or 3-fragment recombination reactions, add 2-3 \u03bcl to 50 \u03bcl of Mix & Go Chemically Competent<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> E. coli <\/span><span>and incubate on ice for 5-30 minutes.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>For 4-fragment recombination reactions, add 4-5 \u03bcl to 50 \u03bcl of Mix & Go Chemically Competent <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli <\/span><span>and incubate on ice for 5-30 minutes.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":58320,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1066027,"guid":"441E517019FD11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","previous_id":1066025,"previous_guid":"7322B70019FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B7C6B1B7AFEC469A9D6A94125A281B0A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Procedure"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2B8566DF1E054C0581303AF4D4C56843","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 0.5 \u03bcl of the Proteinase K solution to each sample to terminate the<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">reaction. Vortex briefly. Incubate samples at 37\u00b0C for <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"483857EB19FD11EBB41B0A58A9FEAC2A","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":600,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":58320,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":600},{"id":1066028,"guid":"63A2190019FD11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","previous_id":1066026,"previous_guid":"7325280019FC11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CA4A13C446034D91951FA750A68CF21C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transformation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B425E48FC73249FF9A20D1CA23FF20DB","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 200 \u03bcl of SOC medium and incubate at 37\u00b0C for 1-1.5 hour with shaking at 225-250 RPM. Can be omitted with Ampicillin resistance.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":58320,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1066064,"guid":"E845D3D019FE11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","previous_id":1066028,"previous_guid":"63A2190019FD11EBA9FC5F704E9F6740","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B26E0CB604994FDBA2F26B668D2A0E13","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transformation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"592E6504637648B19E6E6558C94E00D0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Plate entire reaction on selective media.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"9B47D83A8F584E4C8DF41857F59D8036","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Typical Numbers of Colonies (per 10 \u03bcl reaction):<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\"><\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2-fragment recombination reaction: 2,000-15,000<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3-fragment recombination reaction: 1,000-5,000<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">4-fragment recombination reaction: 50-500<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"22290EB7AB5A4F5D8C53B5B1E2AFC351","order_id":3,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:justify\">Some labs have found that clear colonies contain the correct clone >99% of the time, while opaque colonies never contain the correct clone. A reaction that has worked well will have a clear to opaque colony ratio of at least 3:1. However, as long as clear colonies can be identified, the correct clone will be isolated. Clones can be tested via restriction digest or colony PCR.<\/div><style>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  .justify:after {\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    content: \"\";\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    display:inline-block;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    width: 100%;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  }\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/style><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":58320,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Gateway\u00ae LR Clonase\u2122 II Plus<\/span><span><\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:justify\">Gateway\u00ae LR Clonase\u2122 II Plus enzyme mix is a proprietary enzyme formulation specifically designed for MultiSite Gateway\u00ae and MultiSite Gateway\u00ae Pro. Gateway\u00ae LR Clonase\u2122 II Plus enzyme mix contains the bacteriophage lambda recombination proteins Integrase (Int) and Excisionase (Xis), and the E. coli encoded protein Integration Host Factor  IHF) (1), and reaction buffer provided in a single mix for convenient reaction set up. Gateway\u00ae LR Clonase\u2122 II Plus enzyme mix promotes in vitro recombination between attL- and attR-flanked regions on entry clones and destination vectors to generate attB-containing expression clones.<\/div><style>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  .justify:after {\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    content: \"\";\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    display:inline-block;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    width: 100%;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  }\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/style><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1603987774}